f\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528310\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528310\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hoo1665702920766.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hoo1665702920766.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hoo1665702920766.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hoo1665702920766\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Occurrence-Level Validation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__occurrence_level_validation_139620\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">An occurrence may contain both fields and inner entities. It is possible to select between validating an occurrence with, or without, its inner entities.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__p_d45278e1_d45279e1_d45280e1\">The conditions for occurrence validation are either:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22517e1_d22518e1_d22519e1\">The data of one or more fields in the occurrence has been modified, and the occurrence has not yet been validated successfully, or\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22520e1_d22521e1_d22522e1\">Validation is demanded for the occurrence by setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occcheck</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__topic_d29387e1_d29388e1_d29389e1_d29390e1_d29391e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d926903e68\">\n                       \n Excluding Inner Entities\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__p_d45284e1_d45285e1_d45286e1\">Validating an occurrence without validating the inner entities can be initiated in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22523e1_d22524e1_d22525e1\">By the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span> ProcScript statement.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22526e1_d22527e1_d22528e1\">By an event that changes focus, such as going to the next occurrence with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">^NEXT_OCC</code> structure editor function.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__p_d45287e1_d45288e1_d45289e1\">The process for validating an occurrence without validating the inner entities is as follows:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22529e1_d22530e1_d22531e1\">Uniface validates the primary key.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22532e1_d22533e1_d22534e1\">Uniface validates all candidate keys.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22535e1_d22536e1_d22537e1\">Uniface validates all non-key fields.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22538e1_d22539e1_d22540e1\">Uniface activates the validate trigger for the occurrence.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__topic_d29392e1_d29393e1_d29394e1_d29395e1_d29396e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d926903e110\">\n                       \n Including the Inner Entities\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__p_d45293e1_d45294e1_d45295e1\">Uniface can be instructed to validate an occurrence including its inner entities in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22541e1_d22542e1_d22543e1\">By the <code class=\"ph codeph\">validate/o</code> ProcScript statement\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22544e1_d22545e1_d22546e1\">As part of the validation of a higher level\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__p_d45296e1_d45297e1_d45298e1\">The process for validating an occurrence including its inner entities is as follows:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22547e1_d22548e1_d22549e1\">Uniface validates all inner entities.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hoo1665702920766__li_d22550e1_d22551e1_d22552e1\">Uniface validates the outer occurrence using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hnz1719661363571.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occcheck</a><p>Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702576896.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>validateocc</a><p>Validate an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrk1665702576500.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Validate</a><p>Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528310\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528310\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Occurrence-Level Validation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Occurrence-Level Validation An occurrence may contain both fields and inner entities. It is possible to select between validating an occurrence with, or without, its inner entities. The conditions for occurrence validation are either: The data of one or more fields in the occurrence has been modified, and the occurrence has not yet been validated successfully, or Validation is demanded for the occurrence by setting $occcheck . Excluding Inner Entities Validating an occurrence without validating the inner entities can be initiated in the following ways: By the validateocc ProcScript statement. By an event that changes focus, such as going to the next occurrence with the ^NEXT_OCC structure editor function. The process for validating an occurrence without validating the inner entities is as follows: Uniface validates the primary key. Uniface validates all candidate keys. Uniface validates all non-key fields. Uniface activates the validate trigger for the occurrence. Including the Inner Entities Uniface can be instructed to validate an occurrence including its inner entities in the following ways: By the validate/o ProcScript statement As part of the validation of a higher level The process for validating an occurrence including its inner entities is as follows: Uniface validates all inner entities. Uniface validates the outer occurrence using validateocc . Related Links $occcheck Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence. validateocc Validate an occurrence. Validate Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}